  "text": "There was a decline in the number of functional leaves as the fruit approached maturity (Figure 2 ). This was not surprising as this is directly linked to translocation of nutrients as into fruits during fruit -filling as well as the high susceptibility of the landrace to diseases. The most destructive of these diseases being Black Sigatoka caused by M. fijiiensis as indicated by [CITATION_1] , IITA (1992) .",
