    "167497530": {
      "title": "Sensory Evaluation of Some Hybrid Cooking Bananas in Ghana",
      "abstract": "There are efforts to introduce productive cooking bananas (Musa ABB) to Ghana to complement plantain (Musa AAB), whose production faces several constraints. The consumer acceptability of five popular food preparations namely chips, fried ripe fruits, Ampesi (boiled mature green fruits), Kakro (a doughnut), Ofam (a cake), from four introduced cooking bananas (Saba, FHIA25, FHIA-03, BITA 3) and a dessert banana (Yangambi km 5) was compared with those prepared with a local false horn plantain, Apantu. All the dishes received 100% approval when they were prepared from Apantu. Whereas more than 80% of the panelists who evaluated the dishes found Krakro and Ofam prepared from all the varieties to be very good or good, only BITA 03 was accepted as Ampesi. All the introduced varieties except Saba were given high scores as chips. Introduction of cooking bananas into Ghana is likely to succeed if preparation of processed foods such as Krakro and Ofam from the fruits is widely adopted."
    }
